TEST GUIDE

Steps

The server can be tested via any REST client such as PostMan, Curl, Specialised API Testing clients such as TestMace, etc., or even a web browser.

This Console REST client can serve as basic automated(scriptable) test client.

Edit Config.yml

Copy or input the Actions you want for a test scenario. The Actions can be any combination of

  • getAPIKEY,getCourse,addCourse,updateCourse,deleteCourse,getCourses
  • or Wait(anyduration)

Not all Actions require APIKEY, but all CRUD Actions do need it.

Edit *.req file

Some request carries a json payload.
Edit the respective .req file. Refer to the provided *.req files for samples.

Run gocrudapi-client.exe

Run the client with or without -url flag.
gocrudapi-client.exe -url=https://127.0.0.1:5555 - will hit the dockerised instance
gocrudapi-client.exe - will default to https://127.0.0.1:5000 which will be the local instance.

Just hit Enter to begin run. Test results are appended to test.log

Inspect Test.log

Finally, open the test.log file to inspect the results.
